<DOC><DOCNO> AP901115-0003 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-11-15-90 0017EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i BC-Thailand-Quake     11-15 0152</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Thailand-Quake,0151</SECOND><HEAD>Earthquake Hits Andaman Sea Off Indonesia</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A strong earthquake centered offIndonesia's Sumatra island shook much of southern Thailand onThursday but there were no reports of damage or injuries,Thailand's Meteorological Department said.   The quake measured 6.0 on the Richter scale and was centered inthe Andaman Sea abut 410 miles southwest of Thailand's southernisland of Phuket, the department said.   It said it had received reports that tremors were felt inhigh-rise buildings in Phuket and nearby Songkhla province as wellas in Bangkok.   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by anearthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on aseismograph.   Every increase of one number means the ground motion is 10 timesgreater. A magnitude 6 can cause severe damage in populated areas,while a magnitude 7 can inflict widespread, heavy damage.</TEXT></DOC>